And we've heard it before.

18:36.273 --> 18:38.150
These incendiary accusations

18:38.275 --> 18:42.070
have been used for a generation
to shame and smear

18:42.195 --> 18:43.989
Republicans, conservatives,

18:44.114 --> 18:46.324
Christians and patriots.

18:46.449 --> 18:49.494
Is voting for Trump
like voting for Hitler?

18:49.619 --> 18:52.872
Did Trump win because
of fascism and white supremacy?

18:52.997 --> 18:58.001
Did he revive the worst strains
of America 's history of racism?

18:58.127 --> 19:00.212
Wouldn't that justify the left

19:00.337 --> 19:02.631
in rejecting the results
of the election?

19:04.591 --> 19:07.594
But if they're wrong,
if America is good,

19:07.719 --> 19:10.263
aren't we morally obligated
to defend her?

19:10.388 --> 19:12.515
The stakes could not be higher.

19:12.640 --> 19:16.602
We're talking about the fate of
the greatest nation on Earth.

19:16.727 --> 19:19.438
Who are the real fascists?

19:19.563 --> 19:22.566
Who are the real racists?

19:22.691 --> 19:25.318
We must learn the truth.

19:25.443 --> 19:27.570
For progressives today,

19:27.695 --> 19:29.364
fascism is on the right,

19:29.489 --> 19:33.034
a philosophy of nationalism
and authoritarianism.

19:33.159 --> 19:36.870
They call Trump a fascist
because he's a nationalist.

19:36.996 --> 19:39.039
But so was
my countryman, Gandhi.

19:39.164 --> 19:41.875
So was Mandela
and Winston Churchill.

19:42.000 --> 19:44.085
Lincoln was a nationalist.

19:44.210 --> 19:45.920
Were these men fascists?

19:46.046 --> 19:48.756
We've had authoritarian leaders
since the beginning of time,

19:48.881 --> 19:50.758
but few were fascists.

19:50.883 --> 19:53.886
Look, Trump gets flayed
in the media every day.

19:54.011 --> 19:57.473
Real authoritarians
would have shut that down.

19:57.598 --> 19:59.975
So authoritarianism
and nationalism

20:00.100 --> 20:02.811
don't exhaust the meaning
of fascism.

20:02.936 --> 20:05.730
To go deeper, I sat down
with progressive historian

20:05.855 --> 20:07.857
Robert Paxton,

20:07.982 --> 20:09.567
former head
of Columbia University's

20:09.692 --> 20:11.736
history department.

20:11.861 --> 20:15.614
Paxton is no fan
of Donald Trump.

20:15.739 --> 20:18.617
We have a group
in America today, Antifa...

20:20.827 --> 20:22.120
...which fashions itself

20:22.245 --> 20:23.371
anti-fascist.

20:23.497 --> 20:25.749
- Yes. -It drive speakers
off the campus.

20:25.874 --> 20:29.127
Outwardly, it seems like
there is some resemblance

20:29.252 --> 20:30.253
to Mussolini's Blackshirts.

20:30.378 --> 20:33.047
And the mission
appears the same.

20:33.172 --> 20:36.717
In other words, to enforce a
kind of ideological conformity

20:36.842 --> 20:39.261
by roughing up your opposition.

20:39.386 --> 20:41.847
Do you see a parallel
between Antifa

20:41.972 --> 20:44.683
and the fascists that they
claim to be fighting?

20:44.808 --> 20:47.227
I think there's
some tactical overlap.

20:47.352 --> 20:48.770
As soon as you start, uh,

20:48.895 --> 20:50.897
wearing a uniform
and beating people up,

20:51.022 --> 20:52.940
you're obviously
in fascist territory.

20:53.065 --> 20:55.151
Now, does fascism matter today?

20:55.276 --> 20:57.152
- Yes.
- Some people have said

20:57.277 --> 20:59.154
we are living through
a fascist moment,

20:59.279 --> 21:01.656
or a fascist strain,
in American politics.

21:01.782 --> 21:03.492
Are you worried
that that's true?

21:03.617 --> 21:06.911
The fascist label
seems to me to overlook

21:07.036 --> 21:08.663
two very important differences.

21:08.788 --> 21:10.415
One is that fascist regimes

21:10.540 --> 21:12.208
did not want a free economy.

21:12.333 --> 21:13.959
They had a regulated economy,

21:14.085 --> 21:16.670
and they had
what was called corporatism,

21:16.795 --> 21:19.882
uh, the... and all
the business enterprises

21:20.007 --> 21:23.635
were required to participate
in five-year plans,

21:23.760 --> 21:27.931
and that is the opposite
of what's going on.

21:28.056 --> 21:30.683
So the principles
of the American founding--

21:30.808 --> 21:32.893
the separation
of state and society,

21:33.019 --> 21:34.728
- Mm-hmm.
- limited government,

21:34.854 --> 21:36.522
- Yes.
- Individual rights,

21:36.647 --> 21:40.317
property rights, free markets--

21:40.442 --> 21:43.028
would you agree that this is
what the fascists hated?

21:43.153 --> 21:45.030
The fascists,
and a lot of other people,

21:45.155 --> 21:47.157
believed that these things
had failed,

21:47.282 --> 21:49.617
and they were... they, uh,
were determined to propose

21:49.742 --> 21:52.370
an alternative that
would revive their country.

21:52.495 --> 21:53.788
NEWSREEL NARRATOR:
Dateline Rome.

21:53.913 --> 21:56.165
October 31, 1922.

21:56.290 --> 21:58.459
<i>Italy was</i> a <i>sitting duck
for an ex-Communist</i>

21:58.584 --> 22:00.210
named Benito Mussolini.

22:00.335 --> 22:01.962
The lantern-jawed
founder of fascism

22:02.087 --> 22:04.422
took advantage of
the political unrest in Italy

22:04.547 --> 22:05.840
after World War I.

22:05.965 --> 22:07.884
Mussolini directed
a march on Rome.

22:12.346 --> 22:14.640
The next step was
complete dictatorial control,

22:14.765 --> 22:16.642
a step which the Italian
Blackshirt leader

22:16.767 --> 22:18.811
took without a second thought.

22:18.936 --> 22:20.979
D'SOUZA:
When Mussolini started out,

22:21.104 --> 22:22.230
he was a Marxist.

22:22.355 --> 22:24.024
- He was a socialist.
- Yes.

22:24.149 --> 22:25.692
He was the editor
of the socialist newspaper.

22:25.817 --> 22:27.360
- Yes.
- He had a long background

22:27.485 --> 22:28.486
in socialist politics, right?

22:28.611 --> 22:29.529
Right, right. Exactly.

22:29.654 --> 22:30.696
Mussolini allied himself

22:30.822 --> 22:32.156
with an intellectual,

22:32.281 --> 22:33.657
- Giovanni Gentile.
- Yes.

22:33.783 --> 22:35.576
D'SOUZA:
Gentile famously said,

22:35.701 --> 22:38.245
"Everything in the state,
and nothing outside the state."

22:38.370 --> 22:40.706
- Yes. -Which Mussolini
himself later repeated.

22:40.831 --> 22:43.250
How would you interpret
this doctrine

22:43.375 --> 22:46.461
of sort of
centralized state power?

22:46.586 --> 22:50.048
Mussolini, uh, and the people
who rallied to his cause--

22:50.173 --> 22:52.466
and this included
some highly educated people

22:52.592 --> 22:53.926
like Giovanni Gentile--

22:54.051 --> 22:55.719
they were absolutely determined

22:55.844 --> 22:58.514
to make Italy strong,
and it would come about

22:58.639 --> 23:00.390
by a central authority

23:00.515 --> 23:03.185
and direction,
and I think that the state,

23:03.310 --> 23:06.229
uh, was the instrument
by which they thought

23:06.354 --> 23:08.898
that, uh, Italy
would be regenerated.

23:09.023 --> 23:11.150
And loyalty to the state
is the vehicle

23:11.275 --> 23:13.944
-to mobilize that inner soul,
right? -Yes.

23:21.702 --> 23:23.578
D'SOUZA:
Mussolini was responding

23:23.703 --> 23:26.790
to what historians called
the Crisis of Marxism.

23:28.750 --> 23:31.043
Marx predicted
that worker revolts would erupt

23:31.169 --> 23:34.171
in every
industrialized country.

23:34.296 --> 23:36.882
But this never took place.

23:37.007 --> 23:39.384
Marx thought workers
around the world

23:39.510 --> 23:41.511
would identify with each other

23:41.636 --> 23:43.597
on the basis of class.

23:43.722 --> 23:45.682
He rejected nationalism,

23:45.807 --> 23:48.434
saying a working man
has no country.

23:50.103 --> 23:53.189
But Gentile,
though himself a socialist,

23:53.314 --> 23:55.608
noticed that during World War I

23:55.733 --> 23:58.402
working men fought
for their own country.

23:58.527 --> 24:00.737
Mussolini and Gentile concluded

24:00.862 --> 24:03.865
that a new type
of socialism was needed

24:03.990 --> 24:08.244
that would fuse nationalism
and socialism.

24:08.369 --> 24:10.746
They called it "fascism."

24:10.872 --> 24:15.084
<i>And this is why socialists
and progressives in America,</i>

24:15.209 --> 24:17.795
many of whom had given up
on orthodox Marxism,

24:17.920 --> 24:19.546
were drawn to fascism.

24:19.671 --> 24:20.922
FRANKLIN ROOSEVELT:
In the working out

24:21.048 --> 24:23.758
of a great national program

24:23.884 --> 24:26.344
that seeks the primary good
of the greater number...

24:26.469 --> 24:28.346
D'SOUZA:
Our new president at the time,

24:28.471 --> 24:31.224
Franklin Delano Roosevelt,
was infatuated

24:31.349 --> 24:33.517
by Mussolini.

24:33.642 --> 24:37.980
He called him "that admirable
Italian gentleman."

24:38.105 --> 24:41.274
"I am much interested
and deeply impressed

24:41.400 --> 24:44.236
"by what he has accomplished
and by his evidenced

24:44.361 --> 24:48.114
honest purpose
in restoring Italy."

24:48.239 --> 24:51.450
Mussolini reviewed FDR's book
in an Italian magazine.

24:51.576 --> 24:54.870
His conclusion:
"FDR is one of us.

24:54.995 --> 24:57.039
He's a fascist."

24:57.164 --> 25:00.626
FDR dispatched members
of his brain trust to Rome

25:00.751 --> 25:02.043
to study Italian fascism

25:02.169 --> 25:05.463
with a view to importing
some of it here.

25:05.588 --> 25:08.299
Rexford Tugwell,
one of FDR's closest advisors,

25:08.424 --> 25:11.511
after returning from Italy,
observed:

25:11.636 --> 25:13.763
<i>"Fascism is the cleanest,
neatest,</i>

25:13.888 --> 25:16.724
<i>"most efficient piece
of social machinery</i>

25:16.849 --> 25:19.226
"I've ever seen.

25:19.351 --> 25:20.894
It makes me envious."

25:21.019 --> 25:24.689
The head of FDR's NRA,
or National Recovery Act,

25:24.814 --> 25:27.108
Hugh Johnson, spoke of

25:27.233 --> 25:30.736
the "shining example
of Mussolini, "

25:30.862 --> 25:33.948
he carried fascist literature
in his pocket, and he called

25:34.073 --> 25:37.201
for the end of free-market
capitalism in America.

25:37.326 --> 25:40.579
He empowered industrial
committees in every industry

25:40.704 --> 25:42.873
to set wages and prices

25:42.998 --> 25:44.749
and report
to the federal government.

25:44.874 --> 25:49.670
Clearly, FDR recognized
fascism was on the left.

25:49.796 --> 25:53.174
He saw it as more progressive
than the New Deal.

25:53.299 --> 25:55.801
Mussolini was clearly
a man of the left.

25:55.926 --> 25:59.012
But what about the ultimate
fascist of them all,

25:59.138 --> 26:00.347
Adolf Hitler?

26:00.472 --> 26:02.766
Was he a man of the left?

26:02.891 --> 26:05.852
To figure this out,
we must go to Europe.

26:21.283 --> 26:23.535
Hitler, like Mussolini,
was a veteran

26:23.660 --> 26:25.578
of World War I.

26:26.955 --> 26:28.623
His politics were formed

26:28.748 --> 26:31.250
here in Schwabing,
in the atmosphere

26:31.375 --> 26:34.003
of bohemianism
and sectarian socialism.

26:36.463 --> 26:39.633
The Communist Lenin
lived here in exile.

26:39.758 --> 26:42.427
Hitler and Lenin
both frequented the same pub.

26:42.552 --> 26:45.722
Lenin famously
didn't pay his bar tab.

26:45.847 --> 26:48.808
Imagine Lenin sitting here
arguing with friends

26:48.933 --> 26:51.435
on how to save Communism.

26:51.561 --> 26:54.522
Lenin lived
just a block up the street.

26:54.647 --> 26:57.274
Hitler lived a block over.

26:57.399 --> 27:00.694
Hitler changed the name
of the German Workers' Party

27:00.819 --> 27:04.572
to the National Socialist
German Workers' Party.

27:04.698 --> 27:08.409
The very term "Nazi"
is a compression of two words:

27:08.534 --> 27:12.121
"national " and "sozialista. "

27:12.246 --> 27:15.666
Check out the official
Nazi platform:

27:15.791 --> 27:18.335
State-controlled health care.

27:18.460 --> 27:21.713
Profit sharing for workers
in large corporations.

27:21.838 --> 27:25.216
Money lenders and profiteers
punished by death.

27:25.342 --> 27:27.385
State control of education.

27:27.510 --> 27:29.971
State control
of media and the press.

27:30.096 --> 27:32.473
State control of banks
and industries.

27:32.598 --> 27:34.975
Seizure of land
without compensation.

27:35.100 --> 27:37.353
State control
of religious expression.

27:37.478 --> 27:39.771
This reads like something
jointly written

27:39.897 --> 27:42.357
by Elizabeth Warren
and Bernie Sanders.

27:42.482 --> 27:43.817
Read the Nazi platform

27:43.942 --> 27:45.902
at the Democratic
National Convention,

27:46.027 --> 27:49.155
and most likely it would
provoke thunderous applause.

27:49.280 --> 27:53.034
Like Mussolini and Lenin,
Hitler was anti-big business,

27:53.159 --> 27:56.036
anti-bourgeois
and anti-capitalist.

27:56.161 --> 28:00.624
But unlike Mussolini and Lenin,
Hitler was also a racist.

28:00.749 --> 28:03.919
His racism, too,
was rooted in his hatred

28:04.044 --> 28:06.296
of capitalism and business.

28:06.421 --> 28:08.798
He called the Jews
"greedy bankers."

28:08.923 --> 28:11.801
Hitler set out
to destroy the Jews,

28:11.926 --> 28:14.970
confiscate their wealth
and redistribute it

28:15.095 --> 28:19.558
through Nazi socialist
and welfare state programs.

28:23.353 --> 28:27.315
Another group Hitler hated
were the Communists.

28:30.068 --> 28:31.944
Not because
they were socialists,

28:32.069 --> 28:35.531
but because they took
their orders from Moscow.

28:35.656 --> 28:39.993
His thuggery started right here
at Schellingstrasse 50,

28:40.118 --> 28:42.579
Hitler's Nazi headquarters.

29:00.887 --> 29:04.766
Hitler saw the Communists
as traitors to Germany.

29:18.112 --> 29:20.364
He was a National Socialist,

29:20.489 --> 29:23.033
and they were
International Socialists.

29:26.995 --> 29:29.038
He patterned his Brownshirts

29:29.163 --> 29:32.041
both on Mussolini's Blackshirts
and on the Ku Klux Klan.

29:38.213 --> 29:40.215
The Nazi Brownshirts
and the Klan

29:40.340 --> 29:44.177
were both about the same size--
two to three million members.

29:44.302 --> 29:47.764
Both groups targeted
a vulnerable minority."

29:47.889 --> 29:50.058
in the case
of the Brownshirts, Jews;

29:50.183 --> 29:53.144
in the case of the KKK, blacks.

30:00.025 --> 30:03.653
And both groups were extensions
of a political party:

30:03.778 --> 30:07.574
in the case of the Brownshirts,
the Nazi Party;

30:07.699 --> 30:11.577
in the case of the Klan,
the Democratic Party.

30:19.001 --> 30:22.671
In November of 1923,
Hitler and his Brownshirts

30:22.796 --> 30:24.881
took over
the Burger Brau Keller,

30:25.006 --> 30:28.092
a popular Munich beer hall.

32:02.554 --> 32:04.264
D'SOUZA:
The following day, Hitler

32:04.389 --> 32:06.641
and 2,000 party members
marched on Munich

32:06.766 --> 32:08.059
to seize control.

32:08.184 --> 32:09.894
They were met by police.

32:10.019 --> 32:13.689
Hitler was arrested
and sent to Landsberg Prison,

32:13.814 --> 32:16.984
a formative period in his life.

32:18.318 --> 32:20.862
Here, Hitler dictated
Mein Kampf

32:20.988 --> 32:23.740
to his fellow prisoner,
Rudolf Hess.

32:47.262 --> 32:49.055
See how remote all of this is

32:49.180 --> 32:50.765
from the principles
of Abraham Lincoln

32:50.890 --> 32:53.017
and the American founding?

32:53.142 --> 32:55.728
Hitler, however,
had a much greater affinity

32:55.853 --> 32:59.189
for progressives and Democrats.

33:14.745 --> 33:16.288
It was here

33:16.413 --> 33:19.499
Hitler got a big idea
from the Democratic Party,

33:19.625 --> 33:22.419
one that would shape
his murderous campaigns.

33:23.920 --> 33:26.339
According to Pulitzer
Prize-winning biographer

33:26.464 --> 33:30.343
John Toland, Hitler often
praised the extermination

33:30.468 --> 33:34.680
of the "red savages" who could
not be tamed by captivity.

33:34.805 --> 33:38.517
Hitler admired
how Jacksonian Democrats

33:38.642 --> 33:41.103
"gunned down
the millions of redskins

33:41.228 --> 33:43.396
"to a few hundred thousand,

33:43.522 --> 33:46.774
"and now keep the modest
remnant under observation

33:46.900 --> 33:48.860
in a cage."

33:50.528 --> 33:53.572
His idea was to do
to the Poles, the Slavs,

33:53.698 --> 33:55.950
the Eastern Europeans
and the Russians

33:56.075 --> 34:01.621
precisely what the Jacksonian
Democrats did to the Indians.

34:06.960 --> 34:09.587
Hitler came to power in 1933.

34:11.172 --> 34:13.049
Heil Hitler!

34:13.174 --> 34:15.176
On the other side
of the Atlantic,

34:15.301 --> 34:17.678
another charismatic leader,

34:17.803 --> 34:20.138
FDR, was elected.

34:20.264 --> 34:23.058
The two men
recognized each other

34:23.183 --> 34:26.018
as fellow progressives.

34:26.143 --> 34:29.355
Here's what the Nazi newspaper,
Volkischer Beobachter,

34:29.480 --> 34:32.650
said of the FDR administration."

34:32.775 --> 34:35.277
"We, too,
as German National Socialists,

34:35.402 --> 34:38.822
are looking toward America."

34:38.947 --> 34:41.533
The Nazi paper
congratulated FDR

34:41.658 --> 34:46.079
for replacing the uninhibited
frenzy of market speculation

34:46.204 --> 34:48.706
with the adoption
of National Socialist

34:48.831 --> 34:50.833
strains of thought.

34:50.958 --> 34:54.170
Of FDR's New Deal,
the Volkischer Beobachter said:

34:54.295 --> 34:58.549
"We fear only the possibility
that it might fail. "

35:02.135 --> 35:06.055
Hitler quickly consolidated
his power.

35:06.181 --> 35:08.975
He executed leaders
of the Brownshirts

35:09.100 --> 35:10.977
who had challenged
his authority.

35:11.102 --> 35:13.729
This was the famous
Night of the Long Knives.

35:17.900 --> 35:20.193
Some progressives
try to portray Hitler

35:20.319 --> 35:23.613
as a right-winger
by insisting he was anti-gay.

35:27.367 --> 35:30.536
But Hitler knew that the
Brownshirt leader, Ernst Rohm,

35:30.661 --> 35:35.207
was a notorious homosexual,
as were many other Brownshirts.

35:36.917 --> 35:40.170
When Hitler showed up
to arrest Rohm...

35:40.295 --> 35:42.881
he encountered
a remarkable scene.

35:44.299 --> 35:46.634
Heil, mein Fuhrer!

35:53.724 --> 35:56.518
Rohm publicly suggested
that he, not Hitler,

35:56.644 --> 35:59.313
was the true leader
of the Nazi Party.

36:09.364 --> 36:11.782
When Heinrich Himmler
urged Hitler

36:11.908 --> 36:16.578
to purge the gay Brownshirts
out of the Nazi movement,

36:16.704 --> 36:18.413
Hitler refused.

36:18.539 --> 36:22.834
Hitler said he didn't care what
the Brownshirts did in private,

36:22.959 --> 36:24.961
as long as they were
good fighters.

36:28.047 --> 36:31.717
Hitler was no
social conservative.

36:31.842 --> 36:34.678
Earlier, we saw what Hitler
learned from the Democrats.

36:34.804 --> 36:35.971
But was there anything

36:36.096 --> 36:38.599
he learned from
American progressives?

36:38.724 --> 36:41.893
Investigative journalist
Edwin Black,

36:42.018 --> 36:45.313
the son of Holocaust survivors,
is the author

36:45.438 --> 36:47.774
of The War Against the Weak.

36:47.899 --> 36:50.401
Now, you have written
that eugenics in America--

36:50.526 --> 36:53.529
and this is true in other parts
of Europe as well--

36:53.654 --> 36:56.782
was a progressive CEIUSG.

36:56.907 --> 36:59.243
Progressive in what sense?

36:59.368 --> 37:01.078
Progressive in every sense.

37:01.203 --> 37:02.621
This was not done by people

37:02.746 --> 37:04.581
who thought that
they were race haters.

37:04.706 --> 37:06.499
This was done
by the do-gooders,

37:06.624 --> 37:10.211
the liberals, the people
who wanted to improve society.

37:10.336 --> 37:15.299
Margaret Sanger, a progressive
who wanted to help humanity.

37:15.424 --> 37:17.468
And her approach to doing that

37:17.593 --> 37:20.762
was to wipe away the existence
of two-thirds of all people.

37:20.887 --> 37:23.473
You mean two-thirds of
the entire American population?

37:23.598 --> 37:25.392
- Yes, of course.
- And she actually

37:25.517 --> 37:27.310
- explicitly said this?
- Of course.

37:27.435 --> 37:29.645
She wanted to get rid
of "human weeds."

37:29.771 --> 37:31.939
She wrote about this
extensively.

37:32.064 --> 37:33.899
<i>At one point,
Hitler wrote fan mail</i>

37:34.024 --> 37:36.277
to one of her colleagues
on her board

37:36.402 --> 37:39.279
and said, uh,
"Your writings are my bible."

37:39.404 --> 37:40.697
Uh, this is Madison Grant,

37:40.822 --> 37:43.325
the head of the New York
Zoological Society.

