38:17.314 --> 38:19.274
While we were
pussyfooting around,

38:19.399 --> 38:22.527
the Nazis were beating us
at our own game.

38:22.652 --> 38:23.987
Why is it the case today,

38:24.112 --> 38:26.865
if I open
a Planned Parenthood brochure,

38:26.990 --> 38:30.660
I get a completely different
picture of Margaret Sanger

38:30.785 --> 38:32.536
than anything
that you've described?

38:32.662 --> 38:34.705
What's going on
is the reshaping

38:34.830 --> 38:36.624
and the falsifying of history.

38:36.749 --> 38:39.126
The Nazis
also invented history.

38:39.251 --> 38:40.919
There's a role
for people like me

38:41.044 --> 38:42.712
and a role for people like you.

38:42.838 --> 38:47.050
We spend our lives trying to
authenticate the real history.

38:48.384 --> 38:49.635
D'SOUZA:
We've learned how Hitler

38:49.761 --> 38:51.888
got his murderous
conquest scheme

38:52.013 --> 38:53.597
from the Jacksonian Democrats.

38:53.723 --> 38:56.767
We've also learned
how he got eugenics schemes

38:56.892 --> 38:58.435
from left-wing progressives.

39:00.103 --> 39:04.733
But what does Nazi racism owe
to the Democratic Party?

39:04.858 --> 39:08.653
I went to see the historian
and sociologist Stefan Kuhl,

39:08.778 --> 39:11.155
who has developed
an international reputation

39:11.280 --> 39:14.033
for books like
The Nazi Connection.

39:14.158 --> 39:16.327
I met with him in Munich.

39:17.828 --> 39:20.080
What was the essence
of the Nuremberg Laws?

39:20.205 --> 39:21.373
These are the laws of 1935.

39:21.498 --> 39:24.793
What did they seek to do?

39:24.918 --> 39:27.670
KUHL: They actually gave,
uh, the first definition

39:27.795 --> 39:29.714
of what is a Jew.

39:29.839 --> 39:31.757
It was not very easy
for the Nazis

39:31.882 --> 39:33.384
to define what is a Jew.

40:10.001 --> 40:12.420
Amerika?

41:34.662 --> 41:37.247
D'SOUZA:
The Nazi Nuremberg Laws

41:37.373 --> 41:40.250
were directly modeled
on the segregation laws

41:40.375 --> 41:42.794
of the Democratic Party.

41:42.919 --> 41:45.755
Every segregation law
in the American South

41:45.880 --> 41:48.758
was passed
by a Democratic legislature,

41:48.883 --> 41:50.802
signed by
a Democratic governor

41:50.927 --> 41:54.388
and enforced
by Democratic officials.

41:54.513 --> 41:56.932
As for the Democratic
one-drop rule,

41:57.057 --> 42:01.436
incredibly, the Nazis found it
too racist even for them.

42:04.189 --> 42:05.732
As is well known,

42:05.857 --> 42:08.901
the Nazis also hated
freedom of speech.

42:09.027 --> 42:12.029
The Nazi concept was called
Gleichschaltung,

42:12.154 --> 42:16.241
which means bringing all the
cultural institutions in line

42:16.367 --> 42:18.035
with Nazi ideology.

42:18.160 --> 42:20.037
This was the significance

42:20.162 --> 42:22.497
of the "Heil Hitler" salute

42:22.622 --> 42:26.668
and the draping of
swastika flags off balconies.

42:26.793 --> 42:29.629
These things signaled
humble conformity

42:29.754 --> 42:32.423
to Nazi doctrine.

42:39.513 --> 42:42.015
And what happened
to dissident views

42:42.140 --> 42:44.184
on the German campus?

43:17.006 --> 43:19.132
- Heil Hitler!
- Heil Hitler!

43:20.509 --> 43:22.469
D'SOUZA:
Movements to crush dissent

43:22.594 --> 43:26.097
can quickly escalate
from episodic violence

43:26.222 --> 43:27.932
to mass murder.

43:28.057 --> 43:30.268
Hitler's
Night of the Broken Glass

43:30.393 --> 43:34.313
was justified as a lawful
confiscation of firearms.

43:35.940 --> 43:38.942
This made Jews defenseless
against Nazi assault.

43:39.067 --> 43:43.863
Then Hitler could carry out his
goal to burn Jewish businesses,

43:43.989 --> 43:45.657
destroy synagogues

43:45.782 --> 43:48.451
and eliminate Jews
as a competitive threat

43:48.576 --> 43:50.536
in the German economy.

43:51.954 --> 43:54.248
Hitler didn't
just target synagogues.

43:54.373 --> 43:56.458
He also targeted
Christian churches.

43:56.583 --> 43:58.460
Many people don't know this,

43:58.585 --> 44:00.837
because they've bought
the progressive line

44:00.962 --> 44:03.215
that Hitler was a Christian.

44:03.340 --> 44:05.425
When coming to power,
Hitler knew he needed

44:05.550 --> 44:07.010
Christian support,

44:07.135 --> 44:10.263
and so he feigned
public belief in Christianity.

44:10.388 --> 44:13.182
But privately,
in a series of recordings,

44:13.307 --> 44:15.726
Hitler railed
against Christianity

44:15.851 --> 44:19.897
as a destructive institution
contrary to science

44:20.022 --> 44:23.942
and the natural law
of survival of the fittest.

44:25.860 --> 44:28.738
Once in office,
Hitler persecuted Christians.

44:28.863 --> 44:30.948
His ultimate aim:
the total destruction

44:31.073 --> 44:33.701
of Christianity in Germany.

44:36.412 --> 44:39.748
As a progressive, Hitler
despised religious liberty.

44:39.873 --> 44:42.292
Nazism was his religion.

44:47.130 --> 44:49.716
With Germany the high altar

44:49.841 --> 44:53.094
and Hitler himself
the new messiah.

44:54.178 --> 44:56.680
Hitler was no Christian.

44:58.891 --> 45:02.561
American progressives cheered
Hitler's rise to power.

45:05.688 --> 45:07.482
They saw fascism,

45:07.607 --> 45:10.359
with its social control
and its glorification

45:10.485 --> 45:12.069
of the centralized state,

45:12.194 --> 45:14.905
as a model for the future.

45:22.454 --> 45:25.373
With total control
of the people in place,

45:25.498 --> 45:28.167
Hitler could now implement
his master plan.

45:35.925 --> 45:39.094
In 1939, he invaded Poland.

45:39.219 --> 45:41.805
Within two years,
he and Mussolini controlled

45:41.930 --> 45:43.223
continental Europe.

45:43.348 --> 45:45.016
Japan was at war with China.

45:45.141 --> 45:48.645
Fascism was on the march
across the world.

45:48.770 --> 45:52.356
Soon Hitler would declare war
against America.

45:56.694 --> 45:58.821
Once Hitler acquired
war captives,

45:58.946 --> 46:03.658
he saw a way to implement
his own slave plantation,

46:03.783 --> 46:06.286
which he called
the "concentration camp."

46:07.954 --> 46:10.873
Concentration camps,
which were forced-labor camps,

46:10.998 --> 46:14.919
should be distinguished from
death camps, whose sole purpose

46:15.044 --> 46:17.212
was extermination.

46:18.714 --> 46:21.967
What was the origin
of these death camps?

46:22.092 --> 46:24.844
NARRATOR: His Minister
of Interior directed a program

46:24.969 --> 46:29.015
aimed at aged, insane
or incurable Germans,

46:29.140 --> 46:32.059
the so-called "useless eaters."

46:32.184 --> 46:34.854
Thousands were committed
to special institutions.

46:34.979 --> 46:37.815
Few ever returned.

46:37.940 --> 46:39.816
Evidence proves
they were murdered

46:39.942 --> 46:41.401
because they were useless
to the plans

46:41.526 --> 46:43.361
of the Nazi conspirators.

46:44.863 --> 46:47.907
Let's turn
to the Nazi euthanasia laws.

46:48.032 --> 46:50.118
First of all, would it
be accurate to say that

46:50.243 --> 46:51.619
we aren't talking
about real euthanasia?

46:51.744 --> 46:53.788
Without consent,
neither of the parents

46:53.913 --> 46:55.873
nor of the handicapped
himself, yeah.

46:55.998 --> 46:58.125
So euthanasia was
a pure euphemism, just...

46:58.250 --> 47:01.169
Yes. It was killing.
It was killing program.

47:01.294 --> 47:05.090
They started the killing
of mentally handicapped before

47:05.215 --> 47:06.966
on a very low-scale level,

47:07.091 --> 47:08.968
but, uh, started systematically

47:09.093 --> 47:10.970
with the killing
of mentally handicapped

47:11.095 --> 47:13.180
after the beginning
of the Second World War.

47:13.305 --> 47:16.225
And isn't it... isn't it true
to say that the...

47:16.350 --> 47:17.935
some of the personnel

47:18.060 --> 47:20.771
who administered
the euthanasia camps

47:20.896 --> 47:23.940
were also then later deployed

47:24.065 --> 47:25.734
to the so-called death camps

47:25.859 --> 47:28.945
that were used on a much larger
industrial scale?

47:29.070 --> 47:30.738
That's very clear.
We have technolog...

47:30.863 --> 47:32.782
technology transfer
and the personal transfer

47:32.907 --> 47:34.783
from the killing
of mentally handicapped

47:34.909 --> 47:36.201
to the killing of Jews.

47:36.327 --> 47:39.663
And especially
the whole staff operating

47:39.788 --> 47:41.498
the gas chambers, for example.

47:41.623 --> 47:44.250
D'SOUZA: Let me ask you
about Josef Mengele,

47:44.376 --> 47:47.545
the notorious Nazi doctor
at Auschwitz.

47:51.882 --> 47:55.302
When you read about him,
he saw himself as...

47:55.427 --> 47:56.887
as a progressive--

47:57.012 --> 47:59.723
somebody advancing
not only the cause of science,

47:59.848 --> 48:02.767
but the future benefit
to humanity.

48:02.893 --> 48:04.519
KUHL:
Progressive idea was

48:04.644 --> 48:07.313
very strongly part
of the Nazi ideology.

48:07.438 --> 48:09.941
<i>D'SOUZA: Would it surprise you
if I were to tell you</i>

48:10.066 --> 48:13.527
that after the war Mengele
went down to South America,

48:13.652 --> 48:16.363
where he actually had
a sort of career

48:16.488 --> 48:18.574
<i>as an abortionist?</i>

48:18.699 --> 48:19.866
No...!, not at all.

48:21.243 --> 48:23.370
D'SOUZA:
In classic progressive fashion,

48:23.495 --> 48:26.080
Mengele made an easy transition

48:26.206 --> 48:29.792
from one form of killing
to another.

48:36.632 --> 48:38.675
Once American and Allied troops

48:38.800 --> 48:41.762
liberated
the concentration camps...

48:44.931 --> 48:49.060
...once the world saw
these ghostly, emaciated,

48:49.185 --> 48:52.647
starving figures emerge
from those camps,

48:52.772 --> 48:57.067
Nazism, fascism and theories
of racial superiority

48:57.192 --> 49:00.529
were permanently discredited.

49:09.078 --> 49:11.038
Immediately following the war,

49:11.163 --> 49:14.917
in the Nuremberg trials
held here in room 600,

49:15.042 --> 49:18.128
the full horror
of fascist and Nazi atrocities

49:18.253 --> 49:20.172
was put before the world.

49:20.297 --> 49:21.840
<i>MAN:
United States of America</i>

49:21.965 --> 49:23.842
present count one
of the indictment,

49:23.967 --> 49:25.844
that all the defendants
participated

49:25.969 --> 49:29.847
as organizers or accomplices
in a common plan

49:29.972 --> 49:33.350
or conspiracy
to commit crimes against peace,

49:33.476 --> 49:36.812
war crimes
and crimes against humanity.

49:36.937 --> 49:40.190
D'SOUZA: Fascism became the
quintessential reference point

49:40.315 --> 49:41.733
for human evil.

49:49.866 --> 49:51.742
MAN: ...opposition
by political parties

49:51.867 --> 49:54.411
which might defeat or obstruct

49:54.537 --> 49:56.622
the policy of the Nazi Party.

50:05.296 --> 50:08.341
MAN: Hermann Wilhelm Goring,
on the counts of the indictment

50:08.466 --> 50:09.926
which you
have been convicted,

50:10.051 --> 50:13.012
the Tribunal sentences you
to death by hanging.

50:15.389 --> 50:17.933
D'SOUZA: American progressives
were in a panic.

50:19.643 --> 50:22.938
They realized that if future
generations of Americans

50:23.063 --> 50:26.274
knew the intimate connection
between progressivism

50:26.399 --> 50:29.110
and the Democratic Party
on the one hand,

50:29.235 --> 50:31.737
and the fascists and Nazis
on the other,

50:31.862 --> 50:34.448
they would be finished.

50:34.573 --> 50:38.285
And so, taking a page
from Hitler himself,

50:38.410 --> 50:41.580
they settled upon the idea
of a big lie.

50:41.705 --> 50:46.126
First, they would muddle
the meaning of fascism itself.

50:46.251 --> 50:50.254
They would take the socialism
out of National Socialism.

50:50.379 --> 50:54.425
Second, they would move fascism
from the left-wing column,

50:54.550 --> 50:59.012
where it had always belonged,
into the right-wing column.

50:59.137 --> 51:01.848
But we must not believe
that big lie.

51:01.973 --> 51:05.185
The fascists and the Nazis
were always on the left.

51:05.310 --> 51:08.021
They formed
a mutual admiration society

51:08.146 --> 51:09.731
with the American left.

51:09.856 --> 51:12.066
Even worse,
the most destructive

51:12.191 --> 51:15.402
and genocidal schemes
of the fascists and Nazis

51:15.527 --> 51:18.197
were inspired
by American progressives

51:18.322 --> 51:20.615
and the American
Democratic Party.

51:20.741 --> 51:24.286
That is the crushing
historical truth.

51:24.411 --> 51:28.539
<i>Now we go from the left's
big lie about fascism</i>

51:28.665 --> 51:31.417
to its big lie about racism.

51:31.542 --> 51:34.170
Progressive Democrats
typically blame racism

51:34.295 --> 51:36.880
on America,
and on the founding,

51:37.006 --> 51:39.883
but were the founders to blame
for the elaborate system

51:40.008 --> 51:42.511
of slave plantations?

51:42.636 --> 51:46.222
Historian Allen Guelzo
teaches at Gettysburg College

51:46.347 --> 51:49.058
and is the author
of several award-winning books

51:49.183 --> 51:51.102
on the Civil War.

51:51.227 --> 51:52.978
If we speak
of the founders as a whole,

51:53.104 --> 51:55.731
would it be accurate
to say that they believed A)

51:55.856 --> 51:59.193
slavery is on a path
of extinction;

51:59.318 --> 52:02.946
and B) that slavery is a...

52:03.071 --> 52:04.948
a regrettable thing,
a bad thing?

52:05.073 --> 52:06.699
They were confident

52:06.825 --> 52:08.701
that slavery
was going to disappear,

52:08.826 --> 52:10.369
because it is a contradiction

52:10.495 --> 52:13.247
-of our fundamental principles.
- Are you saying

52:13.372 --> 52:17.001
<i>that there really wasn't a...
formal pro-slavery ideology</i>

52:17.126 --> 52:19.002
at the time of the founding?

52:19.127 --> 52:22.214
GUELZO: There's no
pro-slavery philosophy

52:22.339 --> 52:23.798
that works into the founding.

52:23.924 --> 52:26.050
D'SOUZA: The founders
took specific measures

52:26.176 --> 52:27.677
to restrict slavery.

52:27.802 --> 52:30.304
They outlawed the slave trade,

52:30.429 --> 52:33.933
they prohibited slavery in
the vast Northwest Territories,

52:34.058 --> 52:35.935
under the Northwest Ordinance,

52:36.060 --> 52:39.021
and they mounted such
a strong critique of slavery

52:39.146 --> 52:41.356
that by the end
of the founding era,

52:41.481 --> 52:43.441
slavery went
from being a national

52:43.567 --> 52:45.443
to a regional institution.

52:45.568 --> 52:46.861
Then this happened.

52:46.986 --> 52:48.529
NARRATOR:
All over the world, the impact

52:48.655 --> 52:52.074
of this simple invention
was felt almost immediately.

52:52.199 --> 52:55.661
Eli Whitney put together
a few boards and rollers,

52:55.786 --> 52:58.288
and gave the world
a giant industry.

52:58.413 --> 53:00.749
Cotton was king.

53:02.459 --> 53:05.378
D'SOUZA: This new,
expanded plantation system

53:05.503 --> 53:08.840
demanded a political party
to defend its interests."

53:08.965 --> 53:12.134
the Democratic Party.

53:12.259 --> 53:14.011
At the time of the founders,
they thought slavery

53:14.136 --> 53:15.387
was a dying institution,

53:15.512 --> 53:17.264
but in the 19th century,
that had changed.

53:17.389 --> 53:19.224
They now began
to talk about slavery

53:19.349 --> 53:20.642
as a progressive institution.

53:20.767 --> 53:22.310
And why not?

53:22.435 --> 53:25.146
As George Fitzhugh,
one of the principal

53:25.271 --> 53:27.899
pro-slavery propagandists,
argued:

53:28.024 --> 53:30.359
Isn't slavery the same thing

53:30.485 --> 53:33.487
as what we are reading about
among European socialists?

53:33.612 --> 53:36.782
What else is slavery,
Fitzhugh argued,

53:36.907 --> 53:39.493
but a practical form
of socialism?

53:41.536 --> 53:44.914
D'SOUZA: Fitzhugh even tried to
sell his idea to black leaders.

53:45.040 --> 53:46.541
He defends slavery

53:46.666 --> 53:49.794
as an early form
of the welfare state.

53:49.919 --> 53:52.296
Fitzhugh argues
that in slavery,

53:52.421 --> 53:54.048
unlike in capitalism,

53:54.173 --> 53:56.008
the slaves who cannot
provide for themselves

53:56.133 --> 54:00.387
are looked after
from cradle to grave.

54:00.512 --> 54:03.181
If you took the logic
of that argument-- the idea

54:03.306 --> 54:06.309
that the slave plantation
is a kind of extended family,

54:06.434 --> 54:08.561
that from each
according to his abilities

54:08.686 --> 54:10.438
to each according to his need--

54:10.563 --> 54:12.023
Marxian principle--

54:12.148 --> 54:14.066
that this was
not only an excuse

54:14.191 --> 54:17.069
for enslaving black people, but
there was nothing in the logic

54:17.194 --> 54:19.363
that prevented you
from enslaving a white guy.

54:19.488 --> 54:21.073
Why not enslave white people?

54:21.198 --> 54:23.742
Or at least reduce them
to an economic status

54:23.867 --> 54:25.326
little better than that.

54:25.452 --> 54:26.911
Why not also extend slavery

54:27.036 --> 54:29.122
into the Northern, free states?

54:29.247 --> 54:31.332
Lincoln thought he discerned

54:31.457 --> 54:33.334
the hand of a plot here.

54:33.459 --> 54:36.462
Would it be accurate to say
that one of the key differences

54:36.587 --> 54:38.881
between the Republican
and the Democratic Party

54:39.006 --> 54:42.259
is that the one party
is founded on the idea

54:42.384 --> 54:44.886
of keeping the fruits
of your labor,

54:45.011 --> 54:46.679
and the other party
is founded on the idea,

54:46.804 --> 54:49.474
we get to take your stuff,
either for our own use

54:49.599 --> 54:52.059
or because we've got
some other, better use for it?

54:52.184 --> 54:54.979
That became the credo
of the Democratic Party.

54:55.104 --> 54:58.190
D'SOUZA: The great opponent
of the Democratic plantation

54:58.315 --> 54:59.858
was Abraham Lincoln.

54:59.983 --> 55:03.320
In a phrase, Lincoln
described the evil of slavery

55:03.445 --> 55:04.946
at its core.

55:05.071 --> 55:08.074
LINCOLN (dramatized): You toil
and work and earn bread,

55:08.199 --> 55:10.409
<i>and I'll eat it.</i>

55:10.535 --> 55:14.205
Whenever I hear someone
arguing for slavery,

55:14.330 --> 55:17.249
I feel a strong impulse
to see it tried out,

55:17.374 --> 55:19.626
on him personally.

55:19.751 --> 55:22.212
D'SOUZA:
Lincoln ruthlessly exposed

55:22.337 --> 55:25.465
Democratic hypocrisy.

55:25.590 --> 55:28.176
Wolves devouring lambs--

55:28.301 --> 55:31.554
not because it is good
for their own greedy maws,

55:31.679 --> 55:33.681
but because it is good
for the lambs.

55:33.806 --> 55:37.935
<i>GUELZO: For Lincoln,
the fundamental sin of slavery</i>

55:38.060 --> 55:39.311
curiously enough

55:39.436 --> 55:41.730
was not its racial aspect--

55:41.855 --> 55:43.148
that comes after.

55:43.273 --> 55:46.276
The fundamental sin
of slavery is theft.

55:46.401 --> 55:48.277
Because it says:

55:48.403 --> 55:50.530
You work, you toil,

55:50.655 --> 55:53.199
I will take
the proceeds of that.

55:53.324 --> 55:55.868
And Lincoln 's great anxiety
was to point out

55:55.993 --> 55:59.121
how Northern Democrats
had conspired together

55:59.246 --> 56:01.998
with Southern Democrats
to promote justifications

56:02.124 --> 56:06.085
of taking away the fruit
of other people 's labor.

56:06.211 --> 56:08.880
D'SOUZA: Guelzo is exposing
the progressive strategy

56:09.005 --> 56:11.299
of blaming slavery
on the South.

56:11.424 --> 56:13.634
The Northern Democrats
were in league

56:13.759 --> 56:15.386
with the Southern Democrats,

56:15.511 --> 56:18.263
making slavery the sin
not of the South,

56:18.388 --> 56:22.058
nor of America,
but of the Democratic Party.

56:22.184 --> 56:25.603
GUELZO: Northern Democrats were
fully as complicit in this

56:25.728 --> 56:28.356
as Southern Democrats.

56:28.481 --> 56:31.484
<i>D'SOUZA: The powerful New York
Democrat Martin Van Buren</i>

56:31.609 --> 56:35.779
applied the idea of rural
plantations in the South

56:35.904 --> 56:39.700
to urban centers in the North.

56:39.825 --> 56:42.160
